            "title": "An introduction to the law and economics of environmental policy : issues in institutional design",
            "abstract": [
                "Preface / Richard O. Zerbe -- An introduction to the law and economics of environmental policy : issues in institutional design / Timothy Swanson -- Comments on paper by Richard B. Stewart / Richard O. Zerbe -- Can law and economics stand the purchase of moral satisfaction? / Richard O. Zerbe -- Comments on paper by Richard O. Zerbe, Jr. / Andreas Kontoleon -- Individual preference-based values and environmental decision making : should valuation have its day in court? / Andreas Kontoleon, Richard Macrory, Timothy Swanson -- Comment on paper by Andreas Kontoleon, Richard Macrory and Timothy Swanson / Richard B. Stewart -- Toward a total-cost approach to environmental instrument choice / Daniel H. Cole, Peter Z. Grossman -- Comments on paper by Daniel H. Cole and Peter Z. Grossman / Anthony Ogus -- The choice of instruments for environmental policy : liability or regulation? / Marcel Boyer, Donatella Porrini -- Comments on paper by Marcel Boyer and Donatella Porrini / Michael Faure -- The Aarhus convention and the politics of process : the political economy of procedural environmental rights / Susan Rose-Ackerman, Achim A. Halpaap -- Environmental damage insurance in theory and practice / Michael Faure -- Comments on paper by Michael Faure / James Boyd -- The design of marketable permit schemes to control local and regional pollutants / Jonathan Remy Nash, Richard L. Revesz -- Comments on paper by Jonathon Remy Nash and Richard L. Revesz / Daniel H. Cole -- Monitoring for latent liabilities : when is it necessary and who should do it? / Timothy Swanson, Robin Mason -- Comments on paper by Timothy Swanson and Robin Mason / Anthony Heyes -- Financial responsibility for environmental obligations : are bonding and assurance rules fulfilling their promise? / James Boyd -- Comments on paper by James Boyd / Donatella Porrini -- Pollution and penalties / Anthony Ogus, Carolyn Abbot -- Comment on paper by Anthony Ogus and Carolyn Abbot / Richard L. Revesz -- Eight things about enforcement that seem obvious but may not be / Anthony G. Heyes -- Comment on paper by Anthony G. Heyes / Timothy Swanson -- Comments on paper by Susan Rose-Ackerman and Achim A. Halpaap / Farhana Yamin -- Environmental regulatory decision making under uncertainty / Richard B. Stewart. - An Introduction to the Law and Economics of Environmental Policy emphasises the importance of institutional design in addressing social problems. Three important issues concerning institutional design are: policies, instruments, and enforcement. This volume surveys each of the issues, and emphasises the common themes arising in optimal institutional design. These themes include the cost of complex institutional design, and the role of private institutions attaining social objects. This book will be particularly useful to law schools, departments of government, policy or economics, environmental managers and insurance companies",
                "An Introduction to the Law and Economics of Environmental Policy emphasises the importance of institutional design in addressing social problems. Three important issues concerning institutional design are: policies, instruments, and enforcement. This volume surveys each of the issues, and emphasises the common themes arising in optimal institutional design. These themes include the cost of complex institutional design, and the role of private institutions attaining social objects. This book will be particularly useful to law schools, departments of government, policy or economics, environmental managers and insurance companies"
